## Code review

### Point group project

- Can we move `SymEigen3` into `Matrix3D<T>`?
- Fixed: Why does `BasisSet` depend on `LASolver`?
- `src/BasisSet/Internal/Imp/Orbital_DHF_IBS.C::merge_xxx` use `blazem::submatrix`

## Questions

- For atoms it is common to do numerical solution of the radial DE instead of using basis sets.
- Is there a way to fit that solution approach into the framework for this project?
- What if the radial solution is treated as an irrep basis set (IBS) with one basis function?
- An alternate implementation of `UpdateOrbitals` (`src/Orbitals/Internal/Imp/TOrbitals.C`) would then do a numerical radial
  solution for each irrep using the current charge density.

## Major Features

### Convergence acceleration

- Done: Geometric Direct Minimization (GDM)
  - Read up on BFDS method, Numerical Recipes section 10.7
  - Make notes that translate into our notation.
  - The original paper is very hard to follow.
- DIIS singular B
  - Shprd & Minkoff 2007 eq 23. Linear Least Squares gives a much better condition number.
  - Consider SVD and truncating B.
- EDIIS

### DFT upgrade

- Hand code Vosko's exchange.
- Consider separate `Vxc`, `Vex`, and `Vcorr`.
- Reproducing the NIST tests is tricky (various formula ambiguities).

### Perturbation support

- OOD/SOLID architecture for handling perturbations (first and second order).
- Demo first order with SO-coupling for HF and DHF.
- Demo second order with Moller–Plesset (MP2).

### Configuration Interaction

- Full CI?
- Truncated, multi-reference, and ranking by complexity/usefulness.

### Parallel execution

- Consider OpenMP; beware gprof output issues.
- Use LLVM profiling (`-fprofile-instr-generate`, `-fcoverage-mapping`) and Linux `perf` for profiling.
- Use parallel loops over irreps for `AccumulateDirect` and `AccumulateExchange`.

## Molecules basis set upgrade

- Stage 1: Migrate polarized Gaussian basis sets to use `cache_4` abstraction for radial integrals.
- Stage 2: Use evaluator/concepts framework for Polarized/Cartesian Gaussians.
  - Move `Concepts.C` and the abstract Evaluator interface up to the general BasisSet1 level.
  - Migrate polarized Gaussians to three evaluators: hand-coded McMurchie & Davidson, libcint, etc.
- Stage 3–5: additional evaluators, shared four-index loops, documentation (Doxygen), and hosting docs on GitHub.

## Solids

- Plan for solids/lattices; aim for VASP/ABINIT-like targets eventually.
- Investigate conditional deduction of `hmat_t` from `T` to select `blaze::SymmetricMatrix` vs `blaze::HermitianMatrix`.

## Upgrade existing features

### Top level

- Done: Critical review of CMake files.
- Done: Reorg unit testing so tests live in each library (`doc/cmakenotes.md`).
- Hunt for acronyms and document in `Types.C`.

### Dirac/RKB

- 1s orbital not properly normalized.
- Track factors (0.5, c, 2c) for kinetic matrices.

### Atom evaluators

- Gaussian integrals should use recursion with `Fact[n]/pow(2,n)` — consider `constexpr`.

## Clean up

- Simplify `LASolver` internals.
- Sort out PG cache — keep one cache in `DB_cache`.

## OOD Refactor

- Use a `FunctionFitter` instance instead of inheriting from fitted function implementations.
- Redesign fitting so fitted objects contain a `Fitter*`.

